    &lt;Title&gt;A BIG Thank You&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My dad died on ward A11 on Saturday at very hard time as we were not able to see him. I would like to say a big thank you to all the staff, especially the nurses and Drs who kept us up to date on his care and condtion at such a busy time for them.
My only concern was we were unable to connect to his bedside phone in his last few days,  l will never know if he knew we were trying to contact him. Pt phones appear to be run by a private company, when l spoke to the ward clerk with this issue she was unable to help us. I rang the ward the evening before he died and a lovely nurse went to check  the problem, however he was sleeping and sadly passed away in the early hrs. I cannot thank the staff enough for his care. However in these times when famlies cannot visit l think  the hospital should make sure pts bedside phones are working.
&lt;/CommentText&gt;
